title: The Dennis Prager Radio Show MAY-06-2014 TUES
description:
The Dennis Prager Radio Show MAY-06-2014 TUES...PODCAST



Dennis Prager Radio Show
Prager 20140506  3 Ultimate Issues Hour: Science and God

Prager H3: Dennis talks to Amir Aczel, 
            2004 winner of the Guggenheim Memorial Foundation Fellowship;
             currently a research fellow in the history of science at Boston University.
              His new book is Why Science Does Not Disprove God.




Prager 20140506  2 Sweatshops

Prager H2: Dennis talks to Benjamin Powell,
            Professor of Business at Texas Tech University.
             His new book is Out of Poverty: Sweatshops in the Global EconomyÃ¢â‚¬Â¦

           The Greens want to keep Africa energy poor and in poverty.
            Saving the planet is more important than African lives.


Prager 20140506  1 Prayer

Prager H1: The Supreme Court voted 5-4 to allow public prayer
            in a government facility. Good new. But also very scary. Why?
             It was only a 5-4 vote. One more Democratic President,
              one more liberal justice and public pray is done 
               and so is a major component of the American ethos.

             A minor league baseball team outside of Cincinnati
              has banned peanuts from their ballpark.

            The whiney few have too much power over the many.
